          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-136-621A-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-136-621A-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-136-621A-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-1" n="1">Careful Observers may fortell y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Hour,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-2" n="2">(By sure Prognostick) w<hi rend="superscript">ṇ</hi> to dread a Shower:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-3" n="3">While Rain depends y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> pensive Cat gives o'er</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-4" n="4">Her Frolicks, &amp; pursues her Tail no more:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-5" n="5">Returning Home at Night you'll find y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Sink</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-6" n="6">Strike y<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> offended Sense w<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. double Stink;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-7" n="7">If you be wise y<hi rend="superscript">ṇ</hi> go not far to dine,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-8" n="8">You'll spend in Coach-Hire more y<hi rend="superscript">aṇ</hi> save in Wine.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-9" n="9">A coming Shower y<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> shooting Corns presage,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-10" n="10">Old Aches throb, y<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> hollow Teeth will rage.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-11" n="11">Sauntring to Coffee-House is Dulman seen,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-12" n="12">He damns y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Climate, &amp; complains of Spleen.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-13" n="13">Mean while y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> South rising w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> dabbl'd Wings,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-14" n="14">A Sable Cloud athwart y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Welkin flings;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-15" n="15">That swill'd more Liquor y<hi rend="superscript">aṇ</hi> it cou'd contain,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-16" n="16">And like a Drunkard, gives it up again.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-17" n="17">Brisk Susan whips her Linen from y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Rope,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-18" n="18">While y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> first drizzling is born aslope:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-19" n="19">Such is y<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Sprinkling w<hi rend="superscript">cḥ</hi> some careless Quean</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-20" n="20">Flirts on you from her Mop, but not so clean:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-21" n="21">You fly, invoke y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Gods, y<hi rend="superscript">ṇ</hi> turning, stop</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-22" n="22">To rail; She singing, still whirls on her Mop.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-23" n="23">Nor yet y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Dust had shun'd y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> unequal Strife,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-24" n="24">But, aided by y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Wind fought still for Life:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-25" n="25">And wafted w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> its Foe by violent Gust,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-26" n="26">'Twas doubtful w<hi rend="superscript">cḥ</hi> was Rain, &amp; which was Dust.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-27" n="27">Ah! w<hi rend="superscript">rẹ</hi> must needy Poet seek for Aid,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-28" n="28">When Dust &amp; Rain at once his Coat invade?</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-29" n="29">His only Coat, w<hi rend="superscript">rẹ</hi> Dust confus'd w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> Rain,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-30" n="30">Roughen y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Nape, &amp; leave a mingl'd Stain.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-31" n="31">Now in contiguous Drops y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Flood comes down,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-32" n="32">Threat'ning w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> Deluge y<hi rend="superscript">iṣ</hi> devoted Town:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-33" n="33">To Shops in Crowds y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> daggl'd Females fly,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-34" n="34">Pretend to cheapen Goods, but nothing buy.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-35" n="35">The Templer spruce, while ev'ry Spouts abroach,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-36" n="36">Stays till its fair, yet seems to call a Coach;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-37" n="37">The tuck'd up Sempstress walks w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> hasty Strides,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-38" n="38">While streams run down her oil'd Umbrella's Sides.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-39" n="39">Here various Kind, by various Fortune led</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-40" n="40">Commence Acquaintance underneath a Shed.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-41" n="41">Triumphant Tories, &amp; desponding Whigs,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-42" n="42">Forget y<hi rend="superscript">iṛ</hi> Feuds, &amp; join to save y<hi rend="superscript">iṛ</hi> Wigs;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-43" n="43">Box'd in a Chair y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Beau impatient sits,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-44" n="44">While Spouts run clattering o'er y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Roof by Fits;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-45" n="45">And ever &amp; anon w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> frightful Din</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-46" n="46">The Leather sounds, he trembles from within.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-47" n="47">So w<hi rend="superscript">ṇ</hi> Troy Chair-men bore y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> wooden Steed,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-48" n="48">Pregnant w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> Greeks impatient to be freed,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-49" n="49">(Those Bully Greeks, who, as y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Moderns do,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-50" n="50">Instead of paying Chair-men, run 'em thrô.)</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-51" n="51">Lacoon struck y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> out-side w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> his Spear,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-52" n="52">And each imprisond Hero quak'd for Fear.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-53" n="53">Now from all Parts y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> swelling Kennels flow,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-54" n="54">And bear y<hi rend="superscript">iṛ</hi> Trophies w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> 'em as they go:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-55" n="55">Filth of all Hues, &amp; Odours seem to tell,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-56" n="56">What Street they sail'd from, by y<hi rend="superscript">iṛ</hi> Sight &amp; Smell.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-57" n="57">They, as each Torrent drives, w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> rapid Force,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-58" n="58">From Smithfield or S<hi rend="superscript">ṭ</hi> Pulchers shape y<hi rend="superscript">iṛ</hi> Course,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-59" n="59">And in huge Confluent joind at Snow-Hill Ridge,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-60" n="60">Fall from y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Conduit prone to Holborn·Bridg;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-61" n="61">Sweepings from Butchers Stalls, Dung, Guts &amp; Blood,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-62" n="62">Drown'd Puppies, stinking Sprats, all drench'd in Mud,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-136-621A-line-63" n="63">Dead Cats, &amp; Turnip-Tops come tumbling down y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Flood.</l>
          </lg>
